group_a_task_1_internal_read.ITR1:
Create a questionnaire with multiple choice questions, string questions (which the user answering the questionnaire can answer freely with his own words), single choice questions, etc..

This lets the programmer create questions depending on their catgeory and the answer that is expected.

group_a_task_4_feedback.IQF4:
The questions were so simple and straight forward that I thought I missed something.

Always question everything! Human failure (on one owns part) is a given fact.
group_a_task_4_feedback.IQF5:
Due to its nature as a questionnaire language, the 3 categories (singleChoice, answerWith and ask(String)) should be sufficient for most surveys.

However, I would add the function to combine singleChoice/answerWith questions with a "Reason"-string to give the interviewer more insight as to why the user chose the answer they did, which in return gives more information, which is still optional (due to it having to be read by a human), while the actual answer (singleChoice or answerWith) is still readable by a computer/machine.

group_a_task_5_external_read.ETR1:
List data.

Possibly let the user interact with it?
group_a_task_5_external_read.ETR3: An option to sign up; which exam number it is (x out of y possible exams in this semester)

group_a_task_8_feedback.EQF4:
understanding the simplicity. As simple as it is, it feels like it lacks the capabilities to let you add more data. However this could be more that this example was very specific.

The typing was the biggest problem. Copying would have been easier.
group_a_task_8_feedback.EQF5: Don't see much to be extended upon.

group_a_task_9_final.FQ1:
Let us copy text;
This is more of a typing exercise, although through repeating the process for every bit, it makes it more clear.

Questionnaire q = new Questionnaire()
.ask(singleChoice("How often do you watch television shows?", 
	answerWith(oneOf(
				answer("Extremely often").value("extremely"),
				answer("Very often").value("very"),
				answer("Moderately often").value("moderately"),
				answer("Slightly often").value("slightly"),
				answer("Not at all often").value("not")
	))
))
.ask(multipleChoice("Please choose your preferred movie genres from the list below.",
	answerWith(oneOf(
				answer("Action").value("action"),
				answer("Adventures").value("adventures"),
				answer("Comedy").value("comedy"),
				answer("Crime").value("crime"),
				answer("Drama").value("drama"),
				answer("Historical").value("historical"),
				answer("Horror").value("horror"),
				answer("Musicals").value("musicals"),
				answer("Science Fiction").value("science_fiction"),
				answer("War").value("war"),
				answer("Western").value("western")
	))
))
.ask(shortString("Out of all the movies you have ever seen, which is your most favorite?"
))
.ask(longString("Which film do you think should win Best Picture at this year's Academy Awards?"
))
.ask(shortString("Who is your most favorite movie celebrity living today?"
));
